language ESSENCE' 1.0

$ 8-queens problem
$
$ modified from savile rows' nqueens test.

given      n : int
letting    AMOUNT_QUEENS be domain int(0..n)
find       q1: matrix indexed by [ AMOUNT_QUEENS ] of int(0..n)
find       q2: matrix indexed by [ AMOUNT_QUEENS ] of int(-n..n)
find       q3: matrix indexed by [ AMOUNT_QUEENS ] of int(0..2*n)

such that  allDiff(q1), 
           allDiff(q2), 
           allDiff(q3),
           
         $ diagonals
           forAll i : AMOUNT_QUEENS . (
               (q2[i]=q1[i]-i)  /\
               (q3[i]=q1[i]+i)
           )
           
